100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On November 3, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, addressing ongoing tensions in Europe and the Middle East. In the United States, the trial of John T. Scopes, known as the "Monkey Trial," continued to draw national attention, highlighting the clash between science and religion in schools. Meanwhile, in China, the Nationalist government announced a campaign to bring stability to the war-torn country, signaling a shift in political power amid ongoing civil strife.
